Ms. Brown received her undergraduate degree from Husson University, her Masters of Science in Nursing from the University of Pheonix, Arizona, and a Certificate of Advanced Studies in Nursing from the University of Maine.¬† Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Ms. Brown provided skilled nursing home care for Genesis Healthcare.¬† Robert Allen, MD, PCHC‚Äôs Executive Medical Director, states, ‚ÄúPCHC welcomes Tina Brown, FNP, to her new practice at Penobscot Community Health Center on Union Street in Bangor.¬† Patients will find her to be very likeable, thoroughly competent, and will receive excellent care from her in primary care.‚Äù¬†

Ms. Brown is seeing patients at Penobscot Community Health Center; for an appointment please call 945-5247.¬† Penobscot Community Health Center is open seven days per week and, in addition to family medical care, offers Walk-In Care, Pharmacy, Physical Therapy, and Mental Health Services.";s:10:"post_title";s:58:"Tina Brown, FNP-C, Joins Penobscot Community Health Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:56:"tina-brown-fnp-c-joins-penobscot-community-health-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-21 16:34:13";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-21 20:34:13";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:23:"http://pchc.com/?p=1070";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1098";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-23 15:34:24";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-23 19:34:24";s:12:"post_content";s:3349:"¬†The City of Bangor, the Bangor Area Homeless Shelter, Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC), and numerous partner organizations are proud to work together for a collaborative community project, ‚ÄúPines‚Äù Clean Up, as part of the United Way of Eastern Maine‚Äôs Days of Caring, Friday, October 25, 2013.

¬†<b>Event Information</b>

<b>What:</b>¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† ‚ÄúPines‚Äù Clean Up

<b>When:</b>¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† October 25, 2013, 8:30 am

<b>Where:¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† </b>Volunteers will assemble at the Water Tower on Texas Avenue, Bangor.¬† General parking is available in a lot below the water tower.

¬†Clean up of the ‚ÄúPines‚Äù, a wooded area between Texas Avenue, Hammond Street and Interstate 95, is part of an on-going collaborative effort between the City of Bangor, Bangor Police Department, healthcare and social service organizations, and area homeless shelters to address public safety, the health and well-being of area citizens, and the quality of life in Bangor.

¬†Bangor Mayor Nelson Durgin said "This year's Bangor recognition of Days of Caring takes on special meaning as volunteers throughout the community come together to clean up the "Pines".¬† The Pines has been used for decades by homeless persons as an area to "camp out", and the evidence of alcohol abuse, and other substance abuse in this area has created a very unwelcoming plot in our city.¬† With leadership of the Bangor Public Works, Bangor Public Health and Community Services, The Bangor Homeless Shelter, PCHC/Hope House and the United Way, volunteers will enter the area and dispose of many years accumulation of unsightly and unhealthy trash.¬† All are welcome to participate and other participants will include volunteers from St. Joseph Hospital, Maine DOT and Sam's Club who will donate food which will be prepared for lunch by volunteers from the Job Corps.¬† Clearly, this will be a day of caring where these volunteers will really make a difference.‚Äù

Volunteers for the project are still needed!¬† Interested organizations or individuals may sign up at <a href="http://www.volunteermaine.org/">www.VolunteerMaine.org</a> or by calling the Bangor Area Homeless Shelter at (207)947-0092.¬† Volunteers are also welcome to meet at the Water Tower at 8:30 am on October 25.¬† General parking is available in a lot below the water tower.

¬†Volunteers should dress for outdoor weather, wear sturdy footwear (boots suggested) and bring heavy work gloves.¬† Lunch will be provided for all volunteers.¬† Food and drinks donated by Sam‚Äôs Club will be prepared at the Hope House kitchen and served by Penobscot Job Corps Academy students.

¬†Organizations volunteering time, resources and staff for event include:¬†
<ul>
	<li>City of Bangor Police, Public Works, Public Health and Community</li>
	<li>Bangor Area Homeless Shelter</li>
	<li>PCHC</li>
	<li>Hope House, a service of PCHC</li>
	<li>St. Joseph Hospital</li>
	<li>Bangor Gas</li>
	<li>State of Maine Department of Transportation</li>
	<li>State of Maine Department of Corrections</li>
	<li>University of Maine/Orono, Surveying Engineering Technology</li>
	<li>Sam‚Äôs Club</li>
	<li>Penobscot Job Corps Academy</li>
	<li>Federal Aviation Administration</li>
	<li>Casella Waste Systems</li>
	<li>United Way of Eastern Maine</li>
</ul>";s:10:"post_title";s:38:"Bangor Community Partners For Clean Up";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:31:"bangor-community-partners-clean";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-23 15:34:51";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-23 19:34:51";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:23:"http://pchc.com/?p=1098";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}}s:8:"col_info";a:23:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:2:"ID";s:5:"table";s:10:"pchc_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:4;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:1;s:12:"multiple_key";i:0;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:1;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:3:"int";s:8:"unsigned";i:1;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:11:"post_author";s:5:"table";s:10:"pchc_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:2;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:12:"multiple_key";i:1;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:1;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:3:"int";s:8:"unsigned";i:1;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:9:"post_date";s:5:"table";s:10:"pchc_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:19;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:12:"multiple_key";i:0;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:0;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:8:"datetime";s:8:"unsigned";i:0;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:5:"table";s:10:"pchc_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:19;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:12:"multiple_key";i:0;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:0;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:8:"datetime";s:8:"unsigned";i:0;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:12:"post_content";s:5:"table";s:10:"pchc_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:3349;s: